<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The bird of paradise formerly had the name
<spn>Paradisea apoda</spn>, being supposed to have no feet, as these
were wanting in the specimens first obtained from the East
Indies.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

